      {
        "id": 2,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 3,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Exposition",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above This Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "After the attention-grabbing and emotional first scene, the story enters the Exposition. This can be done via flashbacks, dialogue, or time-jumps, but it must be done in a way to keep the tension rising without info dumps. With the reader hooked and curious, the Exposition takes the reader back before the Climax and begins to explain how the Protagonist ended up in such a dire situation. This beat does not have all the Exposition; it is scattered throughout Beats 2, 3, and 4 to maintain interest."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Will you reveal the backstory through flashbacks, dialogue, time-jumps, or a combination?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Give the reader context by showing the Protagonist in their Ordinary World before everything went sideways."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Present the inciting incident and the Protagonist's reaction – did they take up the adventure willingly or not?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Keep raising the tension and the stakes to generate curiosity and a strong emotional connection for the reader."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Don't forget to consider the Protagonist's character arc and how it will transform throughout the story – where did they start, where will they end?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 1 makes up the first 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Exposition occurs around the 5% - 10% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
